node.text:
Avoiding overstriding 🦵We can post your photos and videos in our account, follow the link in our bio @RunningTerritory and we will select your pictures. 

Avoiding overstriding is a super easy way to boost your performance and at the same time decrease the force/impact on your body and limit the risk of injuries. Overstriding is a common running mistake that occurs when you are making ground contact too far in front of your center of mass. To help you avoiding overstriding here are some tips and tricks:

1️⃣ Use your phone for filming you from the side (best is to use the slow-mo function) and take a look at where your foot is landing in relation to your body

2️⃣ a higher cadence (steps/minute) lowers the possibility for overstriding so try running the same speed but with faster (shorter) steps (check out my playlist for the right beats per minute, link on bio :)

3️⃣ Include running uphill (4-5% incline) to your training as it is almost impossible to have overstriding when running uphill as you are forced into a certain running posture. By that you will get the feeling of making ground contact below your hips/center of mass. You can also do these uphill runs as intervals of running uphill for a longer time is hard 🤙

📽 @fabi_horni_tri
🎶 K-391, Alan Walker, Ahrix - End of Time

node.text:
Shoulders + abs 💪 We can promote your photos in our account. Click the link in our bio for instructions: @RunningTerritory.

Dumbbells only boulder shoulders & sculpted abs circuit. 🔥
.
Save this fun one for later!
.
You can crush it from home or the gym! All you need is a set of heavy & light dumbbells & a bench. Don’t have a bench? Lay on the floor with your feet under the couch for exercises 4 & 6 & sit in a regular chair for exercise 5.
.
D E E T S 👇
.
This is one big giant set. Complete 3 rounds of the following exercises. Rest 45 seconds between each exercise or longer, if needed.
.
1️⃣ HIGH PLANK LATERAL + FRONT RAISE = 1 rep
🔥 8 reps each arm
2️⃣ CLEAN & PRESS TO SINGLE ARM PRESS
🔥 8 reps (right + left arm = 1 rep)
3️⃣ FRONT + LATERAL RAISE + REVERSE FLY + UPRIGHT ROW = 1 rep
🔥 8 reps
4️⃣ DECLINE TWISTS W/ ARMS STRAIGHT + BENT
🔥 20 reps total
5️⃣ SEATED ARNOLD PRESS
🔥 10 reps
6️⃣ DECLINE SIT UP PRESSES
🔥10 reps
7️⃣ COMMANDOS
🔥 10 reps each way

📽 @clairepthomas

Single legged stair jumps 💪 Share your posts with us and we will share them in our account. Apply for a feature following the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory 

Back in Bergen and working on getting some explosiveness back by doing single legged stair jumps. Still a long way to go, but the goal is to be able to get all the way to the top on one leg 🤞🏽 

📽 @naomivdbroeck

node.text:
Never give up 💪 Wanna see your content posted in our account? Apply for a feature on runningterritory.com/feature (link in my bio: @RunningTerritory)

It’s never too late to turn your life around. Get out there and make something of yourself! Photo from yesterday’s Star Wars 5k. Today’s the 10k, tomorrows the Half Marathon. (📸: @morbid2marathon)

⁣High Intensity Cardio 💪 We can share your content in our page, check the link in our bio: @RunningTerritory to follow the process. 
⠀
Try this workout for a quick burn to get shredded 🔥⠀
⠀
4 rounds ⠀
30 seconds on⠀
20 seconds off⠀
⠀
1.) Push-up tuck to squat jump ⠀
⠀
2.) Bear press to push-up pop to low squat hold ⠀
⠀
3.) Side kick through push-up burpee ⠀
⠀
4.) Mountain climber to standing crunch ⠀
⠀
📽 @jrokkmedia
🏋️‍♂️ @scott_mathison_
